DAMATURU – Yobe state delegation to the High-level Stakeholders Interactive Session on Child Protection Law(CPL), Violence Against Persons Prohibition Law (VAPP) and Justice Sector Reform Law, today met with Governor Mai Mala Buni in Abuja. The delegation briefed Governor Buni on the developments on the Child Protection Law, VAPP and the Justice Sector Reform Law, and solicited his support for the adoption and implementation of the Laws in the state Governor Buni commended the team for representing the state at the Forum. APC Problems Very APC Problems – Buni Buni Orders Full Enforcement Of Traffic Laws To Curb Road… He charged the delegation to be good Ambassadors of the state and to protect the interest of the people. The delegation under the leadership of the Speaker Yobe State House of Assembly Hon. Ahmed Lawan Mirwa and the state Chief Judge, Justice kashim Gumna Kaigama, also had Hon. Buba Kalallawa, Hon. Commissioners Goni Bukar and Dr. Garba Iliya, Special Adviser on Religious Affairs Ustaz Babagana Malam Kyari, the Chief Imam Yobe Central Mosque, Ustaz Hudu Muhammad and others.